CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 20, reads: "Crawford Grill Duo - Cozy Harris at the piano and Ted Birch, the Blue Monday Serenaders who are appearing each Monday at the Crawford Grill."
TitMainTitle: Guitarist Thedrus "Teddy" Burch, standing with arm on shoulder of Cozy Harris seated at piano, with Paolo Soprani accordion on top of it, and coatrack on left, in interior with plywood covered windows, possibly Crawford Grill No. 1
